User
Admin
Doctor
Nurse
Technician
System Administrator
Healthcare Staff Member
Patient
Organization
System
Have an integrated UI for all modules of the system
The application menu to adjust according to my role
The information show on the 3D visualization module
about room availability is in sync with the schedule
that was generated by the planning module
The information about healthcare staff, operation types,
and operation requests is in sync with the
information entered in the backoffice module
The information about staff's availability and operation schedule
is in sync with the plan generated by the planning module
Register for the healthcare application
Update my user profile
Delete my account and all associated data
Log in to the system using my credentials
Log in to the healthcare system
Create a new patient profile
Edit an existing patient profile
Delete a patient profile
List/search patient profiles by different attributes
Create a new staff profile
Edit a staff's profile
Deactivate a staff profile
List/search staff profiles
Request an operation
Update an operation requisition
Remove an operation requisition
List/search operation requisitions
Add new types of operations
Edit existing operation types
Remove obsolete or no longer performed operation types
List/search operation types
Obtain the better scheduling of a set of operations
(surgeries) in a certain operation room in a specific day
Know till what dimension in terms of number of surgeries
is possible to ask for the better solution.
Obtain a good schedule, not necessarily the better,
in useful time to be adopted.
The deployment of one of the RFP modules
in a DEI VM to be systematic, validating
it on a scheduled basis with the test plan
Clients on the DEI's internal network (wired or via VPN)
to be able to access the solution
Clients listed in the requirement 6.3.2 to be able
to be defined by simply changing a text file
Identify and quantify the risks involved
in the recommended solution.
Define the MBCO (Minimum Business Continuity Objective)
to propose to stakeholders
A backup strategy to be proposed, justified and implemented
that minimizes RPO (Recovery Point Objective)
and WRT (Work Recovery Time).
Define a public folder for all users registered on the system,
where they can read whatever is placed there
Get users with more than 3 incorrect accesses attempts
See a 3D representation of the hospital/clinic floor
See appropriate textures (that is, suitable for use
in representing a hospital or clinic) mapped onto the floor,
walls, and so on
See the hospital/clinic floor illuminated
with ambient and directional light
Control the camera with the mouse
To be sure that the team has good knowledge of the project, how it may affect patients' personal data and if the processing is done according to the law
Notify both users and the responsible authority
in case of a data breach
